  <h2>QuickBooks Invoice Numbers Not Generating</h2>
  <p>
    This issue may occur during the <strong>Send to QuickBooks</strong> operation when
    QuickBooks Online doesn't generate an invoice number.
  </p>

  <h3>Solution</h3>
  <ol>
    <li>Log in to <strong>QuickBooks Online</strong></li>
    <li>Navigate to <strong>Company Settings</strong> (or Account Settings)</li>
    <li>Go to the <strong>Sales</strong> section</li>
    <li>Find <strong>Custom Transaction Numbers</strong></li>
    <li>Switch it <strong>Off</strong></li>
  </ol>

  <h3>Why This Works</h3>
  <p>
    When Custom Transaction Numbers is enabled in QuickBooks, it expects you to provide
    invoice numbers manually. Turning it off allows QuickBooks to auto-generate numbers,
    which works seamlessly with Field Promax.
  </p>

  <h2>Additional Notes</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Work order numbers from Field Promax are displayed in the <strong>memo field</strong> of invoices generated in QuickBooks</li>
    <li>Only <strong>QuickBooks Administrators</strong> can modify these settings</li>
  </ul>

